				<div class="comment-body"><p>I was told that only novels that are published with a publishers advance (hence not via independent publishers)can qualify for Hugo consideration. </p>
<p>Some small publishers are fairly constrained in the amount of money they can advance for published works &#8212; is there a lower limit in the amount of the advance, so the book can qualify? I assume the minimum print run requirement holds, even for small presses?</p>
<p>Victoria<br />
los angeles, CA</p>
