				<div class="comment-body"><p>Ok this a completely random question but I would really love an answer on it and can&#8217;t fine one anywhere else. I was wondering if some one could explain the controversy surrounding &#8220;The Watchmen&#8221; by Alan Moore in 1988. I know it has been the only graphic novel to ever win a Hugo Award and a heard a rumor that it was because the rules were changed after it won. I was wondering if this was true.</p>
</div>

				<div class="reply">
				<a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='index.html?replytocom=103#respond' data-commentid="103" data-postid="11" data-belowelement="comment-103" data-respondelement="respond" aria-label='Reply to Sarah'>Reply</a>				</div><!-- .reply -->
