				<div class="comment-body"><p>Bruce:</p>
<p>4E won two <a href="../../index.html?page_id=68" rel="nofollow">1946 Retro Hugos</a><a> (presented in 1996 by L.A.con III). He also received a <strike>Special Award</strike> </a><a href="http://www.nesfa.org/data/LL/Hugos/hugos1953.html" rel="nofollow">1953 Hugo Award</a> for &#8220;#1 Fan Personality.&#8221;  <strike>This Special Committee Award is not considered to be a Hugo Award, although it was presented at the first Hugo Awards Ceremony.</strike></p>
<p><strong>Update, 30 Jul 2009:</strong> We&#8217;ve corrected the information above about Ackerman&#8217;s first Hugo after clarification from the appropriate WSFS Committee on the subject, but left our original answer intact (but struck out).</p>
<p>&#8211; Kevin Standlee</p>
