				<div class="comment-body"><p>Any fan who is a member of Worldcon is entitled to nominate &#8212; magazine editors are not disqualified!  But we ask *everyone* (not just editors) to nominate the works they think are the best regardless of who published them.</p>
<p>This isn&#8217;t simply a pious hope.  The thousand or so fans who vote for the Hugos each year are pretty savvy and if an editor or author managed to put an unworthy work on the final ballot, it would be noticed and would probably receive embarrassingly few votes.</p>
</div>

